Bitflux (does not support Safari or Opera)
Cross-Browser Rich Text Editor (very simple, supports all major browsers except Opera) [http://www.kevinroth.com/rte/]
eArea (even simpler than RTE. does not support Opera, but good Mac OS X support.) [http://www.sony-youth.com/software/eArea]
fckEditor (does not support Opera or Safari, but looks like a good solution).
obout (looks great, but ASP.net only?)
RTEF: (best so far for our use? has the set of features we need.) [http://www.rtef.info]
